packageMeta.name: purescript-foreign
packageMeta.description: PureScript library for dealing with foreign data (JSON and JavaScript objects)

modules.name: Data.Foreign
modules.comments:
This module defines types and functions for working with _foreign_
data.

declarations.comments:
A type for _foreign data_.

Foreign data is data from any external _unknown_ or _unreliable_
source, for which it cannot be guaranteed that the runtime representation
conforms to that of any particular type.

Suitable applications of `Foreign` are

- To represent responses from web services
- To integrate with external JavaScript libraries.
declarations.title: Foreign

declarations.comments: A type for runtime type errors
declarations.title: ForeignError

declarations.comments:
An error monad, used in this library to encode possible failure when
dealing with foreign data.

modules.name: Data.Foreign.Class
modules.comments: This module defines a type class for reading foreign values.

declarations.comments:
A type class instance for this class can be written for a type if it
is possible to attempt to _safely_ coerce a `Foreign` value to that
type.

Instances are provided for standard data structures, and the `F` monad
can be used to construct instances for new data structures.
declarations.title: IsForeign

declarations.comments: Attempt to read a data structure from a JSON string
declarations.title: readJSON

declarations.comments: Attempt to read a foreign value, handling errors using the specified function
declarations.title: readWith

declarations.comments: Attempt to read a property of a foreign value at the specified index
declarations.title: readProp

declarations.comments:
A type class to convert to a `Foreign` value.

Instances are provided for standard data structures.
declarations.title: AsForeign

modules.name: Data.Foreign.Index
modules.comments:
This module defines a type class for types which act like
_property indices_.

declarations.comments:
This type class identifies types that act like _property indices_.

The canonical instances are for `String`s and `Int`s.
declarations.title: Index

declarations.title: prop

declarations.comments: Attempt to read a value from a foreign value at the specified numeric index
declarations.title: index
